  "market_context": "Weekly candle closed above previous week's high, establishing bullish bias. Price approached 4H fair value gap (IRL) then targeted previous week's high (ERL). Analysis occurred during mid-November price action after a strong weekly close.",
  "key_observation": "Price reached the 4H fair value gap (internal range liquidity), swept it, then formed a change in state of delivery on the 15-minute chart to target the previous week's high (external range liquidity).",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified weekly bullish continuation bias from weekly candle closing above prior week's high.",
    "Step 2: On 4H chart, located the fair value gap (2757.5–2762.5) as internal range liquidity (IRL) and previous week's high (2772.5) as external range liquidity (ERL).",
    "Step 3: Dropped to 15-minute chart to monitor sweep of the 4H IRL and await change in state of delivery (CISD) over the down-close candle that formed the low.",
    "Step 4: Confirmed CISD when price closed above the down-close candle that created the swing low, validating the bullish structure shift.",
    "Step 5: Entered long off the CISD confirmation with stop near the mean threshold (0.5) of the down-close candle body to ensure ≥2R reward to previous week's high (2772.5)."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade achieved 2R profit as price reached the previous week's high target after the CISD entry.",
  "lessons": "Bullish weekly continuations can be traded by identifying 4H IRL (FVG), waiting for price to sweep it, then entering on LTF CISD with stop at mean threshold to target ERL (prior week high) for ≥2R.",
